excerpt: Seafront arts complex & auditorium housed in a landmark building with futuristic, curving design.
detail_description: The Auditorio de Tenerife Adán Martín is a striking arts complex and auditorium located on the seafront. It is housed in a landmark building with a futuristic, curving design. The city of Santa Cruz de Tenerife, where the auditorium is situated, boasts several main landmarks including the Torres de Santa Cruz, Plaza de Espana, and Iglesia de la Concepcion.
name: Auditorio de Tenerife Adán Martín
address: Av. la Constitución, 1, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Started in 1995 on a former landfill, the 12-hectare botanic garden houses hundreds of palm species.
detail_description: Palmetum, established in 1995 on a former landfill, is a 12-hectare botanical garden featuring an impressive variety of palm species and other tropical plants. Situated atop a hill overlooking the sea and the Cesar Manrique Maritime Park, it offers breathtaking views. The gardens showcase over 600 palm trees along with flowering and fruiting tropical plants from around the world.
name: Palmetum
address: Av. la Constitución, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Lush, roomy green space opened in 1926 featuring fountains & a large clock made of flowers.
detail_description: Parque García Sanabria, located in the heart of Santa Cruz de Tenerife, is a spacious urban park that offers a serene escape from the city's lively atmosphere. Established in 1926, it is the largest park in the Canary Islands and boasts lush gardens, charming fountains, and captivating artworks by both local and international artists. Visitors can wander amidst palm trees, exotic flora, and numerous sculptures while admiring the flower-adorned clock. This 6.
name: Parque García Sanabria
address: Unnamed Road, 38004 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Santa Cruz de Tenerife is a port city on the island of Tenerife, in Spain’s Canary Islands. Well-preserved buildings in its old town include the colonial Church of the Immaculate Conception. The 1700s Palacio de Carta has baroque and neoclassical features. In the Old Civil Hospital, the Museum of Nature and Man has interactive displays on the islands. The city’s squares include the central Plaza de España.
detail_description: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, located in Spain's Canary Islands, is a picturesque port city with well-preserved colonial buildings and historic landmarks like the Church of the Immaculate Conception and Palacio de Carta. The city boasts avant-garde architecture, including the striking Tenerife Auditorium and TEA designed by renowned architects. Visitors can explore museums, art galleries, and vibrant squares like Plaza de España.
name: Santa Cruz de Tenerife
address: Spain

detail_description: TEA Tenerife Espacio de las Artes, located in the capital city of Santa Cruz, is a must-visit for art enthusiasts. Designed by Swiss architects Herzog & de Meuron and Canarian Virgilio Gutierrez, this modern-art gallery boasts a striking concrete-clad building inspired by the island's volcanic landscapes. The gallery features a permanent collection of surrealist works by local artist Oscar Dominguez and hosts top-notch touring exhibitions.
name: TEA Tenerife Espacio de las Artes
address: Av. de San Sebastián, 10, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Located in the heart of the city and close to the sea, Plaza de España was constructed in the 20th century on the grounds of the San Cristobal castle from the 16th century. The square is dominated by the Tenerife Island Council building, which houses the main municipal corporation of Tenerife.
name: Plaza de España
address: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Museum tracing islands' natural history, with mummies & artifacts from the native Guanche culture.
detail_description: The Museum of Nature and Archaeology in Santa Cruz de Tenerife is a cultural space that showcases the natural history of the Canary Islands and houses a diverse range of organizations such as the Oscar Dominguez Institute, the Tenerife Photography Centre, and the Island Network Library. This innovative concept offers a unique cultural infrastructure with a strong commitment to contemporary artworks and new technological innovations.
name: Museum of Nature and Archaeology
address: C. Fuente Morales, s/n, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Aquatic center featuring 3 saltwater swimming pools amid waterfalls & palm trees, plus a sun deck.
detail_description: Parque Marítimo César Manrique is a popular aquatic center in Santa Cruz de Tenerife, offering 3 saltwater swimming pools surrounded by waterfalls, palm trees, and volcanic rocks. This 22,000 square meter park also includes sun terraces and a gymnasium for visitors to relax and enjoy the Canarian sunshine. Designed by architect Cesar Manrique, it's adjacent to the Auditorio and offers a selection of bars and restaurants for guests to unwind.
name: Parque Marítimo César Manrique
address: Av. la Constitución, 5, 38005 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: San Cristóbal de La Laguna is a city and municipality in the northern part of the island of Tenerife in the Province of Santa Cruz de Tenerife, on the Canary Islands, Spain. Wikipedia.
detail_description: San Cristóbal de La Laguna, located in the northern part of Tenerife, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and offers an escape from the bustling urban scene. It serves as a gateway to Teide National Park, making it ideal for nature enthusiasts and hikers. The city is also home to the University of Tenerife, providing plenty of cultural attractions.
name: San Cristóbal de La Laguna
address: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Established in 1943, this bustling, traditional venue features produce, meat & seafood sellers.
detail_description: The Mercado Ntra. Señora de África, established in 1943, is a bustling traditional market featuring various stalls and kiosks offering fresh produce, meat, seafood, flowers, fruit, vegetables, dairy products and more. It serves as a major center of food distribution for the whole of Tenerife and is open every day of the week. On Sunday mornings, it hosts a vibrant flea market in addition to its regular offerings.
name: Mercado Ntra. Señora de África
address: Av. de San Sebastián, 51, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Iglesia de Nuestra Señora de la Concepción, located in Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain, is a Catholic church known for its unique architectural design. It stands out as the only church in the Canary Islands with five naves. The city itself offers various attractions such as Plaza de la Candelaria and Plaza del Principe de Asturias, each with its own historical significance.
name: Iglesia Matriz de Nuestra Señora de la Concepción
address: Pl. de la Iglesia, 2, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: This 14,419-hectare scenic nature park features wildlife & dozens of small rural settlements.
detail_description: Parque Rural de Anaga is a breathtaking 14,419-hectare nature park located in the far north of the island. This lush and rugged paradise is characterized by deep ravines, robust mountain ranges with sharp cliffs, and dense woodlands. The park is a biosphere reserve and boasts abundant vegetation, including laurisilva forests that thrive year-round due to the humid climate sustained by trade winds.
name: Parque Rural de Anaga
address: Monte de Las Mercedes, TF-12, Km 6, 38294 La Laguna, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: This old theatre is a great place to see performances of all kinds, including classical and operatic works. The theater's social distancing means that seats are in high demand, so it's best to book ahead.
name: Teatro Guimerá
address: Pl. Isla de la madera, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: 16th-century Roman Catholic church featuring a bell tower with views of the city.
detail_description: Iglesia de la Concepción is a 16th-century Roman Catholic church in Santa Cruz de Tenerife, known for its bell tower offering panoramic views of the city. The city boasts modern structures and is recognized for its pleasant climate, making it an ideal place to enjoy outdoor spaces like parks and plazas year-round.
name: Iglesia de la Concepción
address: Pl. de la Concepción, 10, 38201 La Laguna, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Main pedestrian artery lined with various retailers, including international chains & indie shops.
detail_description: C. del Castillo, the main pedestrian street in Santa Cruz de Tenerife Old Town, is a bustling hub of retail activity. Lined with a mix of international chains and independent shops, it offers a diverse shopping experience for visitors. The street is named after the historic Castillo Cristobal and extends from Weyler Square to Plaza Candelaria Square before culminating at Spain Square. This pedestrian-only thoroughfare provides an enjoyable atmosphere for leisurely strolls and exploration.
name: C. del Castillo
address: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Gallery space for costumes worn in the annual carnival, with video exhibits & dress-up for kids.
detail_description: Casa del Carnaval is a museum in Santa Cruz de Tenerife that showcases the vibrant costumes worn during the annual carnival. The gallery space features video exhibits and even offers dress-up opportunities for kids. Visitors can also opt for a touristic train option, which includes a 45-minute train tour of the capital along with a free visit to Casa del Carnaval. Additionally, there are bus excursions available that provide access to emblematic places, museums, and various streets in the city.
name: Casa del Carnaval
address: C. Aguere, 17, 38005 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Museo de Bellas Artes in Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain is housed in a grand neoclassical building with a striking pink facade. The museum boasts 14 exhibition rooms showcasing paintings from the 16th to the 20th centuries, featuring Spanish, Canarian, and Flemish works including masterpieces by artists such as Ribera, Bruegel, and Sorolla. Notably, the museum offers free admission.
name: Museo de Bellas Artes
address: C. José Murphy, 12, 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Candelaria Square, also known as Plaza de España, is the largest square in the Canary Islands and is situated near the port of Santa Cruz. The square was built on the site where the San Cristobal castle once stood to defend against pirate attacks. It serves as a gathering place for pilgrims and hosts important regional festivities. Visitors can enjoy beautiful music performances, Gospel groups, and Christmas festivities in this vibrant area.
name: Candelaria Square
address: Pl. de la Candelaria, 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Plaza de los Patos is a small square in commemoration of the failed British attempt to conquer the Canary Islands. It is a beautiful place with interesting architecture and history.
name: Plaza del 25 de Julio
address: Av. de Veinticinco de Julio, 4, 38004, 38004 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Puente Serrador is a historic bridge in Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain. It was built by architect Jose Blasco Robles and completed in 1943. The bridge crosses the city's Santos ravine, connecting the Market with the central area of Santa Cruz. Visitors can admire beautiful murals under the bridge and capture stunning photos of this architectural jewel.
name: Puente Serrador
address: 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Plaza de la Candelaria is a vibrant hub where several bustling streets converge. This iconic square is steeped in history, sitting atop the site of the former San Cristobal fortress. At its center stands the striking monument known as the "Triumph of Candelaria," crafted from exquisite Carrara marble and attributed to Italian artist Pasquale Bocciardo.
name: Plaza de la Candelaria
address: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Just a short stroll south of the park, you'll discover the enchanting Plaza del Príncipe de Asturias, a gem in Santa Cruz that has captivated visitors for generations. Established back in 1868, this vibrant square features stunning marble sculptures from Genoa symbolizing spring and summer. The lush Indian laurel trees, surprisingly imported from Cuba rather than India, add to its charm.
name: Plaza del Príncipe de Asturias
address: 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Historical Military Museum of the Canary Islands, located in Santa Cruz, Tenerife, offers a fascinating exploration of the military history of the region. Situated in several buildings, this museum provides insights into the military heritage of Tenerife and the Canary Islands. With free admission, it's a great way to spend time while learning about the area's past.
name: Historical Military Museum of the Canary Islands
address: C. San Isidro, 2, 38001 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Parish of St. Francisco de Asís, located at Plaza San Francisco, 13, 38002 Santa Cruz, is a significant Catholic church in the area. Originally established as a Franciscan convent and later rebuilt in 1680 in the popular Baroque style of the Canary Islands, it boasts an interior with three knaves and various artifacts dating back to the 17th and 18th centuries.
name: Parish of St. Francisco de Asís
address: Plaza San Francisco, 13, 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Bosque Encantado (La Ensillada) - El Pijaral is a magical hike through the laurel forest, also known as the "Enchanted Forest." To access this enchanting experience, visitors must obtain one of the 45 permits available per day. The trail takes about two and a half hours to complete and offers stunning views of the surrounding area. It's important to make reservations in advance, as permits are quickly claimed.
name: Bosque Encantado (La Ensillada) - El Pijaral
address: TF-123, 38129 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Rustic black-sand beach with a clothing-optional section & a few casual kiosks for food & beverages.
detail_description: Playa de Las Gaviotas is a stunning black-sand beach nestled in the northern part of Tenerife, offering a serene escape for those seeking relaxation and adventure. This picturesque spot is framed by rugged cliffs and boasts crystal-clear waters, making it an ideal location for nature lovers. While it's known for its clothing-optional section, visitors can enjoy the tranquil atmosphere with relatively few clothed sunbathers around.
name: Playa de Las Gaviotas
address: Spain

detail_description: Tenerife Horse Rescue, initially dedicated to saving horses, has expanded its mission to provide a secure haven for numerous animals in Tenerife. These include donkeys, dogs, cats, guinea pigs, birds, and more. The facility is staffed by compassionate volunteers who are enthusiastic about animal welfare. Visitors can gain insight into the center's operations and witness the direct impact of their donations.
name: Tenerife Horse Rescue
address: Barriada San Juan 52, 38589, 38589, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Small, lively strip of sand offering access to shopping & dining, plus picturesque views.
detail_description: Playa de la Pinta is a small, family-friendly beach located in Costa Adeje, offering a lively atmosphere with access to shopping and dining options. The beach is enclosed, providing safety for children and calm waters for swimming. It features soft grayish-colored sand and crystal clear waters with little wave action. Visitors can enjoy various services such as sun lounger rentals, umbrella rentals, sporting activities, boat tours, and local shops for souvenirs.
name: Playa de la Pinta
address: 38660 Costa Adeje, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: El Castillo Negro, a stunning historical site nestled in the heart of a lush jungle, offers visitors an immersive experience in ancient Mayan culture. The impressive architecture and intricate carvings on the walls provide a glimpse into the rich history of this once-thriving civilization. As you explore the site, you'll be captivated by the mysterious aura that surrounds El Castillo Negro, making it a must-visit destination for history enthusiasts and adventure seekers alike.
name: El Castillo Negro
address: Calle 302, 6, 38009 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Hiking trails lead through laurel forest in this serene area with platforms for sweeping views.
detail_description: If you're looking for a unique hiking experience in Tenerife, the Sendero de los Sentidos, or Trail of the Senses, is an absolute must. This enchanting trail winds through lush laurel forests and offers stunning viewpoints that will take your breath away. Originally a vital route connecting the historic villages of Anaga and La Laguna, this 1.3 km (0.8 miles) path is not only easy to navigate but also perfect for families with children.
name: Sendero de los Sentidos
address: 38160 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Tenerife, the Circulo de Bellas Artes has undergone a remarkable transformation since 2015, thanks to new management that breathed life back into this cultural gem. Visitors can enjoy an ever-changing array of open exhibitions showcasing local talent and admire a stunning mural located upstairs in the theatre. The first-floor café offers a delightful escape from the bustling pedestrian zone below, providing a jazzy atmosphere where you can unwind while sipping on quality wine at budget-friendly prices.
name: Circulo de Bellas Artes de Tenerife
address: C. del Castillo, 43, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Estadio Heliodoro Rodríguez López is the home ground of CD Tenerife, a 2nd division Spanish football team. The stadium, which is over 100 years old, offers great views from almost every seat and has a capacity of 22,824 seats. It's known for its fabulous mountainous backdrop and the lively atmosphere during matches. While it may not sell out completely, getting tickets early is recommended due to the popularity of some games.
name: Estadio Heliodoro Rodríguez López
address: Calle Dr. Fernando Barajas Prat, Puerta 18B, 38005 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Santa Cruz, Tenerife, the Museo de las Ilusiones Tenerife is a captivating destination that recently opened its doors in a charming former tobacco factory. Visitors like Greta and Oskaras have raved about their experiences here, highlighting how this museum offers an engaging adventure for all ages. With mind-bending optical illusions and interactive exhibits, families can immerse themselves in a world of visual tricks that spark curiosity and laughter.
name: Museo de las ilusiones Tenerife / Museum of illusions Tenerife
address: C. el Pilar, 11, 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: El Tanque, Espacio Cultural is a unique cultural hub nestled within a repurposed oil tank, showcasing the innovative spirit of its community. This remarkable venue hosts thought-provoking exhibitions like Tahiche Diaz's "El enfado de las criaturas," which creatively uses circus imagery to address themes of sustainability and our relationship with living beings. Visitors can immerse themselves in the artistic projects from Canarian artists while enjoying the insights shared by knowledgeable staff members who are passionate about the space.
name: El Tanque, Espacio Cultural
address: C. Adán Martín Menis, s/n, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Palm-fringed, 1.5km beach of imported yellow sand, with loungers, umbrellas, showers & restaurants.
detail_description: Playa de Las Teresitas is a renowned man-made beach in Tenerife, featuring 1.5km of golden-colored sand imported from Africa. Surrounded by palm trees, it offers luxurious amenities such as loungers, umbrellas, showers, and restaurants. Located about 3 miles from Santa Cruz de Tenerife in the northern part of the island, this popular beach attracts locals and tourists alike.
name: Playa de Las Teresitas
address: Spain

excerpt: Volcanic beach set beneath rocky mountains, backed by restaurants serving seafood & local cuisine.
detail_description: Playa del Roque de las Bodegas is a volcanic beach nestled beneath rocky mountains on the north coast of Tenerife. Accessible via winding roads through the Taganana Mountains, the journey offers a sensory experience. The beach boasts stunning views and an atmospheric location, with restaurants serving fresh seafood and local cuisine. However, caution is advised as strong currents make swimming dangerous, and locals warn of annual fatalities.
name: Playa del Roque de las Bodegas
address: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Chinyero Volcano, located in the Reserva Natural Especial del Chinyero, offers a magical and family-friendly hiking experience. The 6.5 km loop provides epic views of Tenerife's newest volcano and takes hikers through pine forests, offering a striking contrast to the desolate landscapes. This easy two-hour hike is suitable for active pensioners and children alike, with manageable elevation gain.
name: Chinyero Volcano
address: 38435 El Tanque, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Arco de Tajao is a natural rock formation located in the east side of Tenerife. It's easily accessible from the TF1 motorway, with a short 10-minute walk from the parking area next to a food truck. The arch offers a picturesque view and is reminiscent of the famous Arches in Utah. Visitors are advised to check wind speeds before visiting, as it can get quite windy.
name: Arco de Tajao
address: 38588, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

excerpt: Underground remains of a 1500s castle & museum with a cannon said to have injured Horatio Nelson.
detail_description: The Castillo de San Cristobal, located in Santa Cruz Bay, is an underground museum showcasing the remains of a 16th-century castle. This historic fortress has witnessed numerous battles throughout its existence, including conflicts involving notable figures such as Admiral Robert Blake and Rear-Admiral Horatio Nelson. The plaza above the castle was constructed in 1929 and underwent a significant redesign in 2006 by the Swiss architecture firm Herzog & de Meuron.
name: Castillo de San Cristobal
address: s/n Plaza de España, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Playa de Roque Bermejo is a hidden gem located on the northeastern tip of Tenerife. Accessible only by foot or boat, this small and beautiful beach offers a serene escape from the crowds. The black sand sparkles against the wavy ocean, while craggy rock formations line the coastline, with the backdrop of Anaga Rural Park's shaggy mountains adding to its allure. To reach this secluded paradise, visitors can embark on a 1.
name: Playa de Roque Bermejo
address: Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Playa de San Blas is a peaceful and charming area in Tenerife, offering a small beach with beautiful views of the sea. The San Blas Commercial Centre provides various dining and entertainment options, while the boardwalk connecting resorts offers a perfect spot for leisurely strolls and coffee breaks. With its quiet atmosphere and scenic surroundings, this gem of a beach is ideal for those seeking relaxation away from the bustling tourist spots on the island.
name: Playa de San Blas
address: Spain

detail_description: Parque La Granja is a charming park that offers various activities for visitors. It features beautiful gardens and pathways, making it an ideal spot for leisurely walks or exercise. Additionally, the park boasts the best and largest skatepark in Tenerife, making it a popular destination for skating enthusiasts. The park's upcoming refurbishment promises to enhance its appeal even further.
name: Parque La Granja
address: Av. de Madrid, 2, 38007 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Parque natural EL Montillo is an impressive discovery, boasting mesmerizing waterfalls, a charming cafe, lush vegetation, and delightful paths for leisurely strolls. The park also provides ample parking spaces. However, the presence of inexplicable barrier tape mars an otherwise perfect ambiance. It features a bustling 3-11 playground teeming with families and children, alongside areas dedicated to adult exercise and older adolescents (12+).
name: Parque natural EL Montillo
address: Calle Carr. San Antonio, 23, 38379 La Matanza de Acentejo, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

name: Ecomuseo
address: TF-373, 1, 38435 El Tanque, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Plaza el chicharro is a picturesque and charming tourist spot that offers a delightful experience for visitors. On Sundays, this lovely place becomes even more enticing as it transforms into a haven for food enthusiasts, offering an array of delectable handcrafted sweets. Not only does it boast mouthwatering treats, but it also captivates with its stunning fish statue, creating a sense of joy and wonder among those who stumble upon it.
name: Plaza el chicharro
address: Pl. del Chicharro, 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Clock Tower Recova is a charming and picturesque market located in a central location, offering a wide variety of traditional stalls. Visitors can find high-quality meat, free-range chicken, fresh seafood with wonderful flavors, as well as an assortment of fruits and vegetables at reasonable prices. The market also features florists, herbalists, and bulk spice shops. Additionally, there is a bar in the square above that serves delicious juices.
name: Clock Tower Recova
address: C. Darias y Padron, 2, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Palacio de Capitanía General de Canarias, known as the Army Museum, presents some challenges for disabled individuals in terms of accessibility. Efforts have been made to minimize damage to the historic buildings while making them more accessible. Depending on one's interests, the museum can be an enjoyable place to visit in Gazi with a variety of exhibits and historical artifacts. However, it is important not to set high expectations as there may be limitations based on personal preferences.
name: Palacio de Capitanía General de Canarias
address: Pl. del Gral. Weyler, s/n, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: The Triunfo de Candelaria, also known as Obelisco de la Candelaria, is a significant sculptural monument in Santa Cruz de Tenerife. It was donated by Bartolome Montanez and complements the marble cross in Plaza de la Pila. The plaza was named after a source that supplied water to the city and ships. This historical site invites visitors to explore its religious significance and enjoy the picturesque views.
name: Triunfo de Candelaria
address: Pl. de la Candelaria, 38002 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

name: Homenaje al Chicharrero
address: Av. de San Sebastián, 51, 38003 Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain

detail_description: Iglesia de Santa Ana is a fantastic church recommended for various events such as communions, baptisms, and weddings. It features a beautiful Baptismal Font and a large outdoor plaza with wide stairs and ramps. The current priest is pleasant, and the masses are endearing. The church is known for its beautiful images and surroundings, making it a lovely place to visit. It's suitable for ecclesiastical celebrations and offers good views of the city from its exterior.
name: Parroquia de Santa Ana de Candelaria
address: C. Sta. Ana, s/n, 38530 Candelaria, Santa Cruz de Tenerife, Spain
